headline: feat: 4K video rendering with hybrid Ken Burns and deadlock fix
body:
Major changes:
- Upgraded video output to 4K resolution (3840x2160)
- Implemented hybrid Ken Burns effect using cv2.warpAffine for smooth frame generation
- Fixed subprocess deadlock by using DEVNULL for stdout/stderr (prevents pipe buffer filling)
- Improved progress reporting with batch-aware ETA calculation
- Added INTER_LINEAR interpolation for faster frame generation
- Added audio lead-in (1s silence before narration starts)
- Enhanced title/credits slides with decorative frame elements

Technical details:
- Hybrid approach: PIL/Pillow for image prep, OpenCV for frame transforms
- 8 parallel workers with batch-based time estimation
- Smoothstep easing for natural zoom motion
- Variety of zoom targets (center, upper, lower) for visual interest

 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)

headline: fix: Production GCS + Vertex AI + auth reliability
body:
- Fix Vertex AI credentials in Lambda: write service account JSON to
  /tmp and set GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS so google.auth.default()
  finds it (genai.Client ignores the credentials parameter)
- Fix hardcoded dev GCS bucket in gcsService.js  now stage-aware
- Fix SQS_PHOTO_PROCESSING_QUEUE_URL being overridden by dotenv plugin
  with dev value  added to serverless.yml dotenv exclude list
- Add 401 retry with force-refresh in frontend API client  on auth
  failure, forces Amplify to refresh the token and retries once
- Add requeue script for photos missing gcsUri (requeue-photos-missing-gcs.js)
- Add .env.prod to .gitignore, update CLAUDE.md with prod deploy instructions
